cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with spoken term detection using neural networks and natural language processing techniques. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also likely as the paper focuses on audio processing and feature extraction. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses neural networks for feature extraction and classification. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper deals with machine learning techniques for speech processing. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is less likely as the paper does not deal with image or video processing, but it is still a possibility as some computer vision techniques may be used for feature extraction.
